sections.content:
7. Section  34B  of  the  principal  Act  is  amended  by  substituting
for  the  word  “wholly”  appearing  in  paragraphs  (4)(a)  and  (4)(b)
the  word  “mainly”.

(a) in  paragraph  (1)(b),  by  substituting  for  the  words
“Employees Provident Fund Ordinance 1951” the words
“Employees  Provident  Fund  Act  1991”;

(a) in  the  definition  of  “approved  operational  headquarters
company”,  by  substituting  for  the  comma  in  paragraph
(c)  a  semicolon;

(b) in  the  definition  of  “chargeable  person”  in  subsection
(1),  by  renumbering  the  existing  subparagraph  (ii)  as
subparagraph  (iii);

“Joint Development Area” has the meaning assigned
thereto by the Malaysia-Thailand Joint Authority Act
1990  [Act  440];’;

(e) in subsection (2), by inserting after the words “Petroleum
Nasional  Berhad”  the  words  “or  the  Malaysia-Thailand
Joint  Authority”;

(a) in subsection (2), by inserting after the word “chargeable”
the words “or the further amount payable under paragraph
9(1)(c)”;
